brot set, appeared 1978 technical paper kleinian groups robert w. brooks peter matelski. mandelbrot set consists points c complex plane generate bounded sequence values recursive relation zn+1 = zn2 + c repeatedly applied starting z0 = 0. boundary set highly complicated fractal, revealing ever finer detail increasing magnifications. boundary also incorporates smaller near-copies overall shape, phenomenon known quasi-self-similarity. ascii-art depiction seen image hints complexity boundary set. advances computing power computer graphics 1980s resulted publication high-resolution color images set (in colors points outside set reflect quickly corresponding sequences complex numbers diverge), made mandelbrot set widely known general public. named mathematicians adrien douady john h. hubbard honor benoit mandelbrot, one first mathematicians study set detail, mandelbrot set closely related julia set, studied gaston julia beginning 1910s. selected pictures...read more... edit know... ...that regular heptagon regular polygon fewest number sides constructible compass straightedge? ...that gudermannian function relates regular trigonometric functions hyperbolic trigonometric functions without use complex numbers? ...that catalan numbers solve number problems combinatorics number ways completely parenthesize algebraic expression n+1 factors? ...that ball cut reassembled two balls size original (banach-tarski paradox)? ...that impossible devise single formula involving polynomials radicals solving arbitrary quintic equation? ...that euler found 59 amicable numbers 2000 years, 3 pairs found him? ...that cannot knot strings 4-dimensions? can, however, knot 2-dimensional surfaces like spheres. showing 7 items 72 moredidyouknow edit wikiprojects mathematics wikiproject center mathematics-related editing wikipedia. join discussion project's talk page. project pages participants current activity manual style conventions essays advice using wikipedia mathematics self-study proofs subp